        "title": "Duplicate string in java",
        "body": "<p>I want to duplicate a String by a given number separated by <code>,<\/code>. For example:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>int i=3;\nString word = \"a\"; \nString result = String.duplicate(word, ',', i);\n\n// result is: \"a,a,a\"\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>I know there is something like that in Ruby but I'm looking in Java. I wrote some code with a loop and then I removed the last char (which is the <code>,<\/code>). I wondered if there is a build-in function.<\/p>\n\n<p>I did write my own function, I just wanted to know if there is build-in for that..<\/p>\n",
