            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1381175386,
            "creation_date": 1381175386,
            "body": "<p>Commons Lang - <a href=\"http://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-lang/javadocs/api-2.6/org/apache/commons/lang/StringUtils.html#repeat%28java.lang.String,%20java.lang.String,%20int%29\">StringUtils#repeat<\/a>:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>StringUtils.repeat(\"a\", \",\", 3);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 19233381,
            "question_id": 19233315
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/oSB8H.gif?s=256",
                "account_id": 1406648,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1334182,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1334182/s4ber",
                "reputation": 1847,
                "display_name": "S4beR",
                "accept_rate": 82
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1381175575,
            "creation_date": 1381175575,
            "body": "<p>why not write a method of your own<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public String duplicate(String word, String separator, int count) {\n\n  StringBuilder str = new StringBuilder();\n  for (int i =0; i &lt; count; i++) {\n    str.append(word);\n    if (i != count - 1) {\n      // append comma only for more than one words\n      str.append(separator);\n    }\n  }\n\n   return str.toString();\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 19233456,
            "question_id": 19233315
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/R8AYO.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 2366187,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 2071828,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2071828/boris-the-spider",
                "reputation": 61396,
                "display_name": "Boris the Spider",
                "accept_rate": 88
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1381175657,
            "creation_date": 1381175352,
            "body": "<p>Nothing in native Java to do this (besides actually doing it obviously):<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public static void main(String[] args) {\n    System.out.println(join(\"a\", \",\", 3));\n}\n\npublic static String join(final String in, final String on, final int num) {\n    if (num &lt; 1) {\n        throw new IllegalArgumentException();\n    }\n    final StringBuilder stringBuilder = new StringBuilder(in);\n    for (int i = 1; i &lt; num; ++i) {\n        stringBuilder.append(on).append(in);\n    }\n    return stringBuilder.toString();\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>In Guava you could do:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Joiner.on(',').join(Collections.nCopies(3, \"a\"))\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 19233373,
            "question_id": 19233315,
            "last_edit_date": 1381175657
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/eec513e70c36ee57b1a1e39fe7de8d45?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 481839,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 895876,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/895876/jason",
                "reputation": 14046,
                "display_name": "Jason",
                "accept_rate": 49
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1381176947,
            "creation_date": 1381176947,
            "body": "<p>Here's a log (n) solution:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public static String join(String string, int n){\n   StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder(string);\n   StringBuilder out = new StringBuilder();\n   sb.append(\",\");\n\n   for (;n&gt;0;n=n&gt;&gt;1){\n        if (n%2==1){\n           out.append(sb.toString());\n        }\n       sb.append(sb);\n   }\n\n   out.deleteCharAt(out.length()-1);\n   return out.toString();\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 19233900,
